OL,4,Csexual misconduct
OL,6,F"I did not intend to cause any
OL,7,Fdistress"
OL,9,FMr Bell, who chose not to contest the
OL,10,Ffindings, issued an apology, stating:
OL,11,F"I apologise for any upset caused to
OL,12,Fthe complainant and wish to make it
OL,13,Fclear that I did not intend to cause
OL,14,Fany distress."
OL,16,FHe acknowledged the impact of the
OL,17,Finvestigation on his political career,
OL,18,Fsaying it played a role in his
OL,19,Fdecision not to seek re-election.
OL,26,@sD@AOUvD@NO]
