OL,4,Csexual misconduct
OL,6,FThe panel rejected Mr Bell's claim
OL,7,Fthat there had been "mutual flirting"
OL,8,F- something denied by the complainant,
OL,9,Fwith the Standards Commissioner noting
OL,10,Fit "would not justify touching without
OL,11,Fspecific consent" in any case.
OL,13,FAlthough Mr Bell chose not to appeal
OL,14,Fthe finding against him, the
OL,15,Fcommissioner has referred his case to
OL,16,Fthe independent panel to decide on the
OL,17,Fappropriate sanction.
OL,19,F"It is in the workplace"
