OL,6,FThe panel noted that his misconduct
OL,7,Fwas aggravated by the fact he "abused
OL,8,Fhis position over power over the
OL,9,Fcomplainant" as both an MP and, at the
OL,10,Ftime, an assistant government whip.
OL,12,FIt also found the complainant felt
OL,13,F"targeted" as she was "young, female
OL,14,Fand a junior member of staff who would
OL,15,Frisk considerable adverse impacts on
OL,16,Fher career if she made a complaint".
OL,18,FThe report added: "It does not reduce
OL,19,Fthe seriousness of the conduct that it
OL,20,Ftook place in a bar.
