OL,6,F"No matter how the respondent or
OL,7,Fothers may view that environment, it
OL,8,Fis in the workplace and is governed by
OL,9,Frules and policies on appropriate
OL,10,Fbehaviour.
OL,12,F"Any Member of Parliament in that
OL,13,Fsetting remains a person with
OL,14,Fparticular power and authority.
OL,16,F"Indeed, sexual misconduct such as
OL,17,Fthis, which is both brazen and
OL,18,Fdrunken, makes the conduct more
OL,19,Fserious as the level of threat is
OL,20,Fincreased."
